<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="13" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[119,768,1695,1962]" lastBlockId="12.[816,1464,135,957]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
The taxonomy of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1838" box="[419,516,1695,1719]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Mesalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[419,516,1695,1719]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Mesalina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been relatively stable over the past decades compared to other Middle 
<collectingRegion box="[689,768,1731,1754]" country="Saudi Arabia" name="Ash Sharqiyah" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Eastern</collectingRegion>
Eremiadini (e.g., 
<taxonomicName box="[303,477,1764,1788]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Acanthodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[303,477,1764,1788]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Acanthodactylus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[491,578,1765,1788]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Eremias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[491,578,1765,1788]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Eremias</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The last species were described in 2002 (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Joger &amp; Mayer" authorityYear="2002" box="[377,454,1799,1823]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Mesalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kuri">
<emphasis box="[377,454,1799,1823]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">M. kuri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Joger, U. &amp; Mayer, W." box="[493,719,1800,1824]" journalOrPublisher="Fauna of Arabia" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="497 - 505" part="19" refString="Joger, U., &amp; Mayer, W. (2002). A new species of Mesalina (Reptilia: Lacertidae) from Abd al-Kuri, Socotra archipelago, Yemen, and a preliminary molecular phylogeny for the genus Mesalina. Fauna of Arabia, 19, 497 - 505." title="A new species of Mesalina (Reptilia: Lacertidae) from Abd al-Kuri, Socotra archipelago, Yemen, and a preliminary molecular phylogeny for the genus Mesalina" type="journal article" year="2002">Joger &amp; Mayer, 2002</bibRefCitation>
; and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Segoli, Cohen, &amp; Werner" authorityYear="2002" box="[119,266,1833,1857]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Mesalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bahaeldini">
<emphasis box="[119,266,1833,1857]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">M. bahaeldini</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Segoli, M. &amp; Cohen, T. &amp; Werner, Y. L." box="[310,508,1834,1858]" journalOrPublisher="Faunistiche Abhandlungen Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde Dresden" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="157 - 176" part="23" refString="Segoli, M., Cohen, T., &amp; Werner, Y. L. (2002). A new lizard of the genus Mesalina from Mt. Sinai, Egypt. Faunistiche Abhandlungen Staatliches Museum fur Tierkunde Dresden, 23, 157 - 176." title="A new lizard of the genus Mesalina from Mt. Sinai, Egypt" type="journal article" year="2002">Segoli et al., 2002</bibRefCitation>
). The taxonomic adjustments recommended herein emphasise how the diversity of a relatively well-known species may actually be underestimated. 
<taxonomicName authority="Jiří Šmíd &amp; Jiří Moravec &amp; Václav Gvoždík &amp; Jan Štundl &amp; Daniel Frynta &amp; Petros Lymberakis &amp; Paschalia Kapli &amp; Thomas Wilms &amp; Andreas Schmitz &amp; Mohammed Shobrak &amp; Saeed Hosseinian Yousefkhani &amp; Eskandar Rastegar-Pouyani &amp; Aurora M. Castilla &amp; Johannes Els &amp; Werner Mayer, 2017" authorityName="Jiří Šmíd &amp; Jiří Moravec &amp; Václav Gvoždík &amp; Jan Štundl &amp; Daniel Frynta &amp; Petros Lymberakis &amp; Paschalia Kapli &amp; Thomas Wilms &amp; Andreas Schmitz &amp; Mohammed Shobrak &amp; Saeed Hosseinian Yousefkhani &amp; Eskandar Rastegar-Pouyani &amp; Aurora M. Castilla &amp; Johannes Els &amp; Werner Mayer" authorityYear="2017" box="[119,367,1937,1961]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Mesalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saudiarabica" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[119,367,1937,1961]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Mesalina saudiarabica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[379,441,1939,1962]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
described here from western Arabia contributes to the intensively growing knowledge on the evolution and systematics of the pan-Arabian reptile fauna within the last years (
<bibRefCitation author="Carranza, S &amp; Simo-Riudalbas, M. &amp; Jayasinghe, S. &amp; Wilms, T. &amp; Els, J." box="[1040,1264,205,229]" journalOrPublisher="PeerJ" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="2371" part="4" refString="Carranza, S., Simo-Riudalbas, M., Jayasinghe, S., Wilms, T., &amp; Els, J. (2016). Microendemicity in the northern Hajar Mountains of Oman and the United Arab Emirates with the description of two new species of geckos of the genus Asaccus (Squamata: Phyllodactylidae). PeerJ, 4, e 2371." title="Microendemicity in the northern Hajar Mountains of Oman and the United Arab Emirates with the description of two new species of geckos of the genus Asaccus (Squamata: Phyllodactylidae)" type="journal article" year="2016">Carranza et al., 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Kapli, P &amp; Lymberakis, P. &amp; Crochet, P. A. &amp; Geniez, P. &amp; Brito, J. C. &amp; Almutairi, M. &amp; Poulakakis, N." box="[1275,1460,205,229]" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Biogeography" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="267 - 279" part="42" refString="Kapli, P., Lymberakis, P., Crochet, P. A., Geniez, P., Brito, J. C., Almutairi, M., … Poulakakis, N. (2015). Historical biogeography of the lacertid lizard Mesalina in north Africa and the Middle East. Journal of Biogeography, 42, 267 - 279." title="Historical biogeography of the lacertid lizard Mesalina in north Africa and the Middle East" type="journal article" year="2015">Kapli et al., 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Metallinou, M &amp; Arnold, E. N. &amp; Crochet, P. - A. &amp; Geniez, P. &amp; Brito, J. C. &amp; Lymberakis, P. &amp; Carranza, S." box="[816,1068,239,264]" journalOrPublisher="BMC Evolutionary Biology" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="1 - 17" part="12" refString="Metallinou, M., Arnold, E. N., Crochet, P. - A., Geniez, P., Brito, J. C., Lymberakis, P., … Carranza, S. (2012). Conquering the Sahara and Arabian deserts: Systematics and biogeography of Stenodactylus geckos (Reptilia: Gekkonidae). BMC Evolutionary Biology, 12 (258), 1 - 17." title="Conquering the Sahara and Arabian deserts: Systematics and biogeography of Stenodactylus geckos (Reptilia: Gekkonidae)" type="journal article" year="2012">Metallinou et al., 2012</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Metallinou, M &amp; Cervenka, J. &amp; Crochet, P. - A. &amp; Kratochvil, L. &amp; Wilms, T. &amp; Geniez, P. &amp; Carranza, S." box="[1085,1140,239,263]" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="208 - 220" part="85" refString="Metallinou, M., Cervenka, J., Crochet, P. - A., Kratochvil, L., Wilms, T., Geniez, P., … Carranza, S. (2015). Species on the rocks: Systematics and biogeography of the rock-dwelling Ptyodactylus geckos (Squamata: Phyllodactylidae) in North Africa and Arabia. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 85, 208 - 220." title="Species on the rocks: Systematics and biogeography of the rock-dwelling Ptyodactylus geckos (Squamata: Phyllodactylidae) in North Africa and Arabia" type="journal article" year="2015">2015</bibRefCitation>
; de 
<bibRefCitation author="de Pous, P. &amp; Machado, L. &amp; Metallinou, M. &amp; Cervenka, J. &amp; Kratochvil, L. &amp; Paschou, N. &amp; Carranza, S." box="[1195,1385,239,263]" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Zoological Systematics and Evolutionary Research" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="67 - 81" part="54" refString="de Pous, P., Machado, L., Metallinou, M., Cervenka, J., Kratochvil, L., Paschou, N., … Carranza, S. (2016). Taxonomy and biogeography of Bunopus spatalurus (Reptilia; Gekkonidae) from the Arabian Peninsula. Journal of Zoological Systematics and Evolutionary Research, 54, 67 - 81." title="Taxonomy and biogeography of Bunopus spatalurus (Reptilia; Gekkonidae) from the Arabian Peninsula" type="journal article" year="2016">Pous et al., 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Smid, J. &amp; Shobrak, M. &amp; Wilms, T. &amp; Joger, U. &amp; Carranza, S." journalOrPublisher="Organisms, Diversity and Evolution" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="267 - 285" part="17" refString="Smid, J., Shobrak, M., Wilms, T., Joger, U., &amp; Carranza, S. (2017). Endemic diversification in the mountains: Genetic, morphological, and geographical differentiation of the Hemidactylus geckos in southwestern Arabia. Organisms, Diversity and Evolution, 17, 267 - 285." title="Endemic diversification in the mountains: Genetic, morphological, and geographical differentiation of the Hemidactylus geckos in southwestern Arabia" type="journal article" year="2017">Šmíd, Shobrak, Wilms, Joger, &amp; Carranza, 2017</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Smid, J. &amp; Carranza, S. &amp; Kratochvil, L &amp; Gvozdik, V. &amp; Nasher, A. K. &amp; Moravec, J." journalOrPublisher="PLoS One, 8" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="64018" part="5" refString="Smid, J., Carranza, S., Kratochvil, L., Gvozdik, V., Nasher, A. K., &amp; Moravec, J. (2013). Out of Arabia: A complex biogeographic history of multiple vicariance and dispersal events in the gecko genus Hemidactylus (Reptilia: Gekkonidae). PLoS One, 8 (5), e 64018." title="Out of Arabia: A complex biogeographic history of multiple vicariance and dispersal events in the gecko genus Hemidactylus (Reptilia: Gekkonidae)" type="journal article" year="2013">Šmíd, Carranza, et al., 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Smid, J. &amp; Carranza, S. &amp; Kratochvil, L &amp; Gvozdik, V. &amp; Nasher, A. K. &amp; Moravec, J." box="[952,1256,303,333]" journalOrPublisher="PLoS One, 8" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="64018" part="5" refString="Smid, J., Carranza, S., Kratochvil, L., Gvozdik, V., Nasher, A. K., &amp; Moravec, J. (2013). Out of Arabia: A complex biogeographic history of multiple vicariance and dispersal events in the gecko genus Hemidactylus (Reptilia: Gekkonidae). PLoS One, 8 (5), e 64018." title="Out of Arabia: A complex biogeographic history of multiple vicariance and dispersal events in the gecko genus Hemidactylus (Reptilia: Gekkonidae)" type="journal article" year="2013">Šmíd, Moravec, et al., 2013</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Smid, J. &amp; Moravec, J. &amp; Kratochvil, L. &amp; Nasher, A. K. &amp; Mazuch, T. &amp; Gvozdik, V &amp; Carranza, S." box="[1271,1460,303,333]" journalOrPublisher="Systematics and Biodiversity" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="346 - 368" part="13" refString="Smid, J., Moravec, J., Kratochvil, L., Nasher, A. K., Mazuch, T., Gvozdik, V., &amp; Carranza, S. (2015). Multilocus phylogeny and taxonomic revision of the Hemidactylus robustus species group (Reptilia, Gekkonidae) with descriptions of three new species from Yemen and Ethiopia. Systematics and Biodiversity, 13, 346 - 368." title="Multilocus phylogeny and taxonomic revision of the Hemidactylus robustus species group (Reptilia, Gekkonidae) with descriptions of three new species from Yemen and Ethiopia" type="journal article" year="2015">Šmíd et al., 2015</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tamar, K. &amp; Carranza, S. &amp; Sindaco, R. &amp; Moravec, J. &amp; Trape, J. - F. &amp; Meiri, S." box="[816,1123,343,368]" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="6 - 18" part="103" refString="Tamar, K., Carranza, S., Sindaco, R., Moravec, J., Trape, J. - F., &amp; Meiri, S. (2016). Out of Africa: Phylogeny and biogeography of the widespread genus Acanthodactylus (Reptilia: Lacertidae). Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 103, 6 - 18." title="Out of Africa: Phylogeny and biogeography of the widespread genus Acanthodactylus (Reptilia: Lacertidae)" type="journal article" year="2016">Tamar, Carranza, et al., 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tamar, K &amp; Scholz, S. &amp; Crochet, P. - A. &amp; Geniez, P. &amp; Meiri, S. &amp; Schmitz, A. &amp; Carranza, S." box="[1132,1417,343,367]" journalOrPublisher="Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="55 - 68" part="97" refString="Tamar, K., Scholz, S., Crochet, P. - A., Geniez, P., Meiri, S., Schmitz, A., … Carranza, S. (2016). Evolution around the Red Sea: Systematics and biogeography of the agamid genus Pseudotrapelus (Squamata: Agamidae) from North Africa and Arabia. Molecular Phylogenetics and Evolution, 97, 55 - 68." title="Evolution around the Red Sea: Systematics and biogeography of the agamid genus Pseudotrapelus (Squamata: Agamidae) from North Africa and Arabia" type="journal article" year="2016">Tamar, Scholz, et al., 2016</bibRefCitation>
). As some of the studies show, cryptic and previously unrecognised species are present along the western Arabian mountains, and more species descriptions from there may thus be expected.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[816,1464,135,957]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
For future taxonomic work on 
<emphasis box="[1176,1278,481,505]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1838" box="[1176,1274,481,505]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Mesalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Mesalina</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
it is important to note that 
<taxonomicName authority="Jiří Šmíd &amp; Jiří Moravec &amp; Václav Gvoždík &amp; Jan Štundl &amp; Daniel Frynta &amp; Petros Lymberakis &amp; Paschalia Kapli &amp; Thomas Wilms &amp; Andreas Schmitz &amp; Mohammed Shobrak &amp; Saeed Hosseinian Yousefkhani &amp; Eskandar Rastegar-Pouyani &amp; Aurora M. Castilla &amp; Johannes Els &amp; Werner Mayer, 2017" authorityName="Jiří Šmíd &amp; Jiří Moravec &amp; Václav Gvoždík &amp; Jan Štundl &amp; Daniel Frynta &amp; Petros Lymberakis &amp; Paschalia Kapli &amp; Thomas Wilms &amp; Andreas Schmitz &amp; Mohammed Shobrak &amp; Saeed Hosseinian Yousefkhani &amp; Eskandar Rastegar-Pouyani &amp; Aurora M. Castilla &amp; Johannes Els &amp; Werner Mayer" authorityYear="2017" box="[915,1083,516,540]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Mesalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saudiarabica" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[915,1083,516,540]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">M. saudiarabica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1092,1149,517,540]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is not any of Arnold’s (1980, 1986c) undescribed south Arabian species (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1838" box="[1295,1390,551,575]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Mesalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1295,1390,551,575]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Mesalina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. A from the mountains of Yemen and Saudi Arabia and 
<emphasis box="[1373,1395,586,609]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">M</emphasis>
. sp. B from Dhofar, Oman). Its presence was not recorded until the material for recent phylogenetic studies (
<bibRefCitation author="Kapli, P &amp; Lymberakis, P. &amp; Crochet, P. A. &amp; Geniez, P. &amp; Brito, J. C. &amp; Almutairi, M. &amp; Poulakakis, N." box="[1234,1415,655,679]" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Biogeography" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="267 - 279" part="42" refString="Kapli, P., Lymberakis, P., Crochet, P. A., Geniez, P., Brito, J. C., Almutairi, M., … Poulakakis, N. (2015). Historical biogeography of the lacertid lizard Mesalina in north Africa and the Middle East. Journal of Biogeography, 42, 267 - 279." title="Historical biogeography of the lacertid lizard Mesalina in north Africa and the Middle East" type="journal article" year="2015">Kapli et al., 2015</bibRefCitation>
; this study) had become available. Further effort should be dedicated to obtaining genetic data from the two supposedly new species mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Arnold, E. N." box="[959,1099,759,784]" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Oman Studies, Special Report" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="273 - 332" part="2" refString="Arnold, E. N. (1980). The reptiles and amphibians of Dhofar, southern Arabia. Journal of Oman Studies, Special Report, 2, 273 - 332." title="The reptiles and amphibians of Dhofar, southern Arabia" type="journal article" year="1980">Arnold (1980</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Arnold, E. N." box="[1108,1172,759,783]" journalOrPublisher="Biological Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" pagination="263 - 281" part="29" refString="Arnold, E. N. (1986 c). Why copulatory organs provide so many useful taxonomic characters: The origin and maintenance of hemipenial differences in lacertid lizards (Reptilia: Lacertidae). Biological Journal of the Linnean Society, 29, 263 - 281." title="Why copulatory organs provide so many useful taxonomic characters: The origin and maintenance of hemipenial differences in lacertid lizards (Reptilia: Lacertidae)" type="journal article" year="1986" yearSuffix="c">1986c</bibRefCitation>
) as well as from two narrowranging species that have not yet been analysed genetically and placed in a phylogenetic framework, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Arnold" authorityYear="1980" box="[1209,1344,829,852]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Mesalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ayunensis">
<emphasis box="[1209,1344,829,852]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">M. ayunensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Lanza &amp; Poggesi, 1975)" authorityName="Lanza &amp; Poggesi" authorityYear="1975" baseAuthorityName="Lanza &amp; Poggesi" baseAuthorityYear="1975" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Mesalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ercolinii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">M. ercolinii</emphasis>
(Lanza &amp; Poggesi, 1975)
</taxonomicName>
. Such data may shed new light on the evolutionary history and hopefully help to untangle relationships within some of the other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1838" box="[1168,1263,932,956]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Mesalina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1168,1263,932,956]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Mesalina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complexes.
